ith OSHA 1910.38(a). Flexitank's Process Safety Management (PSM) program is in process of been review to reach compliance of Program # by December 31, 2014 and it follows the requirements set forth in 29 CFR 1910.119; it also complies with federal, state, and local regulatory requirements; it includes, but it is not limited to the following:

1)    Prevention & Contingency (SOP GI15) and Emergency Response Plans (SOP GI10); which provides guidelines for responding to various emergencies such as fires, hazardous material spills, personal injuries, severe weather events, and property damage that may occur at the Flexitank Depot and headquarters facilities; 

2)    Employees participate (SOP QMD07), at least once a year, on safety and release prevention program; it provides the essential planning and training for effectively protecting our employees, the company, the environment, and the property; before, during and after an emergency situation; 

3)    Training (SOP AD15), is provided for all operations personnel such as: drivers, operators, maintenance, equipment control, general operations and customer service personnel; 

4)    Our emergency response program (ERT) (SOP GI10); includes Spill Containment and an  "in-house" emergency response HAZMAT team (SOP QMD08) and is supported by local Incident and Emergency Response Contractors;

5)    Process Safety Information (SOP GI20) is maintained on ammonia and other hazardous materials;

6)    A Hazard Risk Assessment (SOP GI21)  is conducted periodically to ensure adequacy of controls, and processes; 

7)    The Preventive maintenance program (SOP OP09) ensures the mechanical integrity of the equipment and its pressure relief and vapor control systems continue to operate as designed; 

8)    Operating SOP's (OP02) provides all personnel with the information necessary to safely transport and store equipment;

9)    Contractors or visitors working on our Depot facility require a work permit (SOP OD19) provided by the QHSSE team. As part of the SOP

, all visitors are briefed on the hazards and safety requirements of the job; and are trained to respond in case of release (Safety Briefing SOP GI-05);

10)    Hot Work Permits (SOP OD17) are required whenever welding, cutting, grinding or other activities are conducted that could generate sparks and start a fire;

11)    Formal Incident investigations (SOP GI29) are conducted for incidents involving any and all releases and near misses that endanger employees or the public; 

12)    Compliance Audits (SOP QMD03) are conducted periodically to ensure that the prevention program is meeting its objectives; 

13)    QHSSE -  Management System (PL-041) is in place as Flexitank Quality Policy;

14)    Management of Change (MOC) under SOP AD32 is in place to ensure project success, avoid loss of employees or customer's due to changes and minimize the impact on productivity

15)    Pre-TRIP Safety Review (PTSR) are created "custom made" for ammonia  and other hazardous products or substances. (SOP OD03/0D09)

16)    Departmental / Safety Meetings -QMD02 each department under must perform periodical safety meetings and report finding to the Safety Committee. 

17)    Facility Safety Committee is composed of the top managers of the company and meet periodically to discuss reports. (QMD04)
